menu "ACRouter rbAmp Source (v2.0 sensing)"

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_SOURCE
    bool "Enable rbAmp I2C sensor source"
    default n
    help
        Poll rbAmp sensor modules over the shared I2C bus and feed their
        measurements into the Sensor Hub as an ACROUTER_SOURCE_I2C source
        (priority 0, preferred over the internal ADC).

        This is the v2.0 sensing-offload path: rbAmp modules do the
        current/voltage/power DSP on-device (5 Hz commit), so the ESP32 no
        longer needs local ADC sampling. Additive — runs alongside the
        internal ADC source until ADC is removed in a later phase.

        Safe to enable with no modules present: discovery finds nothing and
        the poll task posts nothing. Requires rbAmp hardware to produce data.

if ACROUTER_RBAMP_SOURCE

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_POLL_MS
    int "rbAmp poll interval (ms)"
    default 200
    range 100 5000
    help
        Fleet poll cadence. rbAmp commits RMS metrics every 200 ms (5 Hz,
        hard floor); polling faster than 200 ms yields no fresher data.

comment "Module role mapping (0x00 = unset). Assigns a discovered module's primary channel to a Sensor Hub slot."

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_GRID_ADDR
    hex "Grid rbAmp module I2C address"
    default 0x00
    help
        7-bit address of the rbAmp module measuring the GRID feed. 0 = none.

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_SOLAR_ADDR
    hex "Solar rbAmp module I2C address"
    default 0x00
    help
        7-bit address of the rbAmp module measuring the SOLAR feed. 0 = none.

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_LOAD_ADDR
    hex "Load rbAmp module I2C address"
    default 0x00
    help
        7-bit address of the rbAmp module measuring the LOAD feed. 0 = none.

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_VOLTAGE_ADDR
    hex "Dedicated voltage rbAmp module I2C address"
    default 0x00
    help
        7-bit address of a voltage-only rbAmp module. 0 = none (grid module's
        voltage is used when it has voltage hardware).

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_AUTOSCAN
    bool "Auto-discover rbAmp modules at init"
    default y
    help
        Scan the bus for rbAmp modules (by PRODUCT_ID) at init and add them
        to the fleet. Discovered modules are polled and logged (diagnostic);
        assign a Sensor Hub role per module via rbamp_source_configure() to
        feed the routing control loop.

config ACROUTER_RBAMP_TASK_WDT
    bool "Subscribe poll task to Task Watchdog"
    default y
    help
        A wedged I2C bus can block the IDF i2c_master driver indefinitely
        (the library cannot interrupt a blocking same-task call). Subscribing
        the poll task to the Task WDT auto-reboots cleanly out of a wedge.
        Recommended for production (rbAmp fleet guidance).

endif

endmenu
